{{Quote|Fighter Control, this is ST-One-One, Lieutenant Vil Dance of TIE fighter Alpha Squadron.|Villian Dance aboard Black-11|<ref name="ds" />}}
'''Black 11''', also known as '''Black-11''', was the designation of a [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/ln starfighter]] in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Black Squadron (Galactic Empire)/Legends|Black Squadron]] which was assigned to the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] [[Steel Talon/Legends|''Steel Talon'']] above the [[Prison/Legends|prison]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Despayre]] prior to the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Frequently used by [[Alpha Squadron]]'s [[Lieutenant Commander/Legends|Lieutenant Commander]] [[Villian Dance]], it was used by Dance to pursue and destroy the [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]] [[RLH-1]] when the [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle]] attempted to escape Despayre. By [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], Black 11 was operated by a [[TIE pilot]] nicknamed "[["Wampa"/Legends|Wampa]]," and stationed aboard the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|Super Star Destroyer]] [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']]. At that [[Time/Legends|time]], Black 11 frequently served as an escort to the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] shuttle, the ''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle [[ST 321/Legends|ST 321]].

==Description==
{{Quote|Go to tactical channel five, that's tac-fiver, and log in.|Villian Dance gives orders while piloting Black-11|<ref name="ds" />}}
Black 11,<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> also known as Black-11,<ref name="ds" /> was a [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/ln starfighter]]<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> manufactured by [[Sienar Fleet Systems/Legends|Sienar Fleet Systems]].<ref name="DB" /> It was powered by [[Twin ion engine/Legends|twin ion engines]] and contained flight control systems, which emitted [[Color/Legends|green]] lights that would turn on when their power-up stud was touched. The [[TIE series/Legends|TIE/LN]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] was additionally armed with twin [[Laser cannon/Legends|laser cannons]] operated by a fire-control button. Black 11 had a hatch that would hiss shut when closed.<ref name="ds" />

At least one [[TIE pilot]] operated Black 11.<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> The starfighter had a communication system that would automatically activate upon startup, and included tactical channel five which was a lower-powered band with a shorter range. Black 11 also had a [[Sensor/Legends|sensor]], with a screen that would ping when the starfighter had spotted a target. Its equipment included thrusters and throttles for movements, and a control panel which would alert the [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] when they reached [[Minimum Safe Distance]]&mdash;the safest distance relative to a [[Gravity well/Legends|gravity well]] at which it could enter [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] without being destroyed.<ref name="ds" />

==History==
===Alpha Squadron===
{{Quote|Attention, shuttle RLH-One. Turn the craft around and proceed immediately to Star Destroyer ''Steel Talon''{{'s}} tractor beam range.|Villian Dance flying Black-11 and communicating to RLH-1|<ref name="ds" />}}
[[File:Villian.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Villian Dance piloted Black 11.]]
Black 11 was attached to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Black Squadron (Galactic Empire)/Legends|Black Squadron]]<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] against the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. Prior to the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], Black 11 was stationed aboard the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] [[Steel Talon/Legends|''Steel Talon'']] above the [[Prison/Legends|prison]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Despayre]]. Docked aboard a [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]] when idle, Black 11 had been frequently used by the Imperial [[Alpha Squadron]]'s [[Commanding officer/Legends|commanding officer]], [[Lieutenant Commander/Legends|Lieutenant Commander]] [[Villian Dance]], who also operated under the [[Callsign/Legends|call sign]] [[ST-1-1]]. Dance had found Black 11 to be one of his favorite TIE/LN starfighters, noting that some were better than others in ways such as being faster and tighter in turns, or having [[Laser/Legends|laser]] [[Cannon/Legends|cannons]] that were quicker to [[Starfighter combat/Legends|fire]].<ref name="ds" />

When a group of [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoners]] on Despayre stole the [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]] [[RLH-1]], Alpha Squadron responded under Dance, who piloted Black 11 in the skirmish that followed. Black 11 caught up to RLH-1, and when the occupants refused to surrender, the starfighter prevented the [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttle's]] escape into hyperspace by destroying it.<ref name="ds" />

===Service on the ''Executor''===
[[File:Avenger-ROTJ.png|thumb|right|300px|Black 11 (right) escorts ST 321 to the Death Star II battlestation.]]
By the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|VI}} to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> Black 11 was stationed aboard the [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']],<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> the Imperial [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|Super Star Destroyer]] that was both the [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] of the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord of the Sith]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and the [[Command ship/Legends|command ship]] of [[Death Squadron/Legends|Death Squadron]].<ref name="RotJ" /> Black 11 often served as an escort to Vader's<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> ''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle, [[ST 321/Legends|ST 321]],<ref name="RotJ" /> and by that [[Time/Legends|time]] was operated by a pilot who was nicknamed "[["Wampa"/Legends|Wampa]]" for their [[Water/Legends|icy]] precision in battle.<ref name="Black 11 Card" />

In 4 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]],<ref name="NEC" /> Black 11 and another TIE/LN starfighter, alongside ST 321, were transported by the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] ''[[Thunderflare]]'' to the [[Endor system/Legends|Endor system]]. The two starfighters then escorted ST 321 to the [[Star system/Legends|system's]] Imperial [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]], [[Death Star II/Legends|Death Star II]], for [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Vader's unannounced visit there shortly before the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].<ref name="RotJ" />

==Commanders and crew==
{{Quote|Copy, Alpha Leader!|Alpha Squadron responding to Villian Dance|<ref name="ds" />}}
When stationed aboard the ''Steel Talon'' prior to the Battle of Yavin, Lieutenant Commander Villian Dance was among the TIE pilots randomly assigned to Black 11. It was a favorite of his, and it was used by him in the mission to destroy the shuttle RLH-1.<ref name="ds" /> By 4 ABY,<ref name="NEC" /> the pilot nicknamed "Wampa" operated Black 11 when it was stationed aboard the ''Executor''.<ref name="Black 11 Card" />

==Behind the scenes==
Black 11 first appeared in the opening scene of [[1983]]'s [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="RotJ" /> The TIE fighter was first named in the [[2000]] ''[[Death Star II Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Decipher]] [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="Black 11 Card" /> The starfighter reappeared in the [[2007]] novel [[Death Star (novel)|''Death Star'']], written by [[Michael Reaves]] and [[Steve Perry]], where it was also given the name Black-11.<ref name="ds" />

[[File:EX49-SWTCG-TESB.png|thumb|right|250px|Black 11's image was reused to represent EX-4-9.]]
A discrepancy exists between the opening scene of ''Return of the Jedi'' and its [[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (novelization)|novelization]] released in the same year. In the novel, several TIE/LN starfighters are described as escorting ST 321 to the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]],<ref name="ROTJnovel">[[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi'' novelization]]</ref> contradicting the film's depiction of only two such starfighters performing that duty.<ref name="RotJ" /> Based on that discrepancy, this article avoids treating the novelization as a confirmed Black 11 appearance, and considers the ''Return of the Jedi'' film as its first appearance.

In [[2003]], a rotated version of Black 11 was used on the [[EX-4-9]] card for the [[The Empire Strikes Back (TCG)|''Empire Strikes Back'']] expansion set of the ''[[Star Wars Trading Card Game]]''. The card image is an altered version<ref name="TCG">{{TCG|set=The Empire Strikes Back|cardname=TIE Fighter EX-4-9|link=https://swtcg.com/Content/Images/Cards/ESB/TIE_Fighter_EX_4_9.webp?v=2}}</ref> of a film still from the [[Hoth asteroid field/Legends|Hoth asteroid field]] in [[1980]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']].<ref name="ESB">{{Film|V}}</ref>

